Title: A Baltic Tragedy
Writer: Johan Bergenstråhle, Per Olov Enquist (novel), Staffan Lamm, Harald Stjerne
Actors: Bo Brundin, Yrjö Tähtelä, Anneli Sauli, Knut Blom
Plot: In 1945 about 3 000 German soldiers and a 167 Baltic legionaries came as refugees to Sweden. Those who came via the island Gotland were first detained there, in a camp next to Havdhem.
